		<container id="swap_content01" behavior="LOCK_SIZE" x="355" y="140" visible="false" fx="SWAP_SHOW" hidefx="SWAP_HIDE" style="">
			<text id="header" x="15" y="0" width="350" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="true" fx="">
				<content translate="true">&lt;B&gt;Praise &lt;/B&gt;</content>
			</text>
			<text id="text" x="0" y="15" width="366" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="true" fx="">
				<content translate="true">&lt;LI&gt;It is important for parents to teach their children what good behavior means and to correct misbehavior. Praise is a method parents can use to help children understand what to do rather than only what not to do.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;When children feel ignored, such as when their parent is on the phone or talking to a friend, it is common for them to misbehave. Encouraging good behavior in these circumstances includes thanking the child for waiting and helping the child find an alternative activity.&lt;/LI&gt;</content>
			</text>
		</container>
		<container id="swap_content02" behavior="LOCK_SIZE" x="355" y="140" visible="false" fx="SWAP_SHOW" hidefx="SWAP_HIDE" style="">
			<text id="header" x="15" y="0" width="350" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="true" fx="">
				<content translate="true">&lt;B&gt;Modeling&lt;/B&gt;</content>
			</text>
			<text id="text" x="0" y="15" width="372" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="true" fx="">
				<content translate="true">&lt;LI&gt;Modeling is defined as showing a child the behavior you would like to see. For example, parents should say "please" and "thank you" if they would like their child to use these words, too.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Children also copy negative behaviors that a parent displays. If a parent makes a mistake, like saying a bad word or losing their temper, the key is for the parent to acknowledge what happened and talk about why it was a mistake. This approach is better for your child than pretending it didn't happen.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Using a consistent approach to model desired behavior as well as acknowledging errors shows children what is expected of them and teaches them it is OK to make mistakes.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
			</text>
		</container>
